<task id="task-2831" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">How to define steps</title><shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">Steps in the feature files must be defined before use.</shortdesc><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context "><p class="- topic/p ">To create new step definitions, do as follows:</p></context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Test Explorer</uicontrol>, navigate to the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Include/scripts/groovy</uicontrol> folder. Right-click and choose <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">New</uicontrol> &gt; <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Step Definition</uicontrol>.</cmd><stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Keyword</uicontrol> dialog appears.</stepresult></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Choose your <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Package</uicontrol>, then enter your <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Class Name</uicontrol>. You can also enable the option to <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Generate sample @Given, @When, @Then steps</uicontrol>.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><image width="500" href="image/ks-840-keyword.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">keyword</alt></image></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Once you are done, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">OK</uicontrol>.</cmd></step></steps><result class="- topic/section task/result ">A new step definition is created.<p class="- topic/p "><image width="750" href="image/ks-840-new-step-definition.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">new step definition</alt></image></p></result></taskbody></task>